-- Yale Names Polak as Provost to Replace President-Elect Salovey
-- B y   J a n e t   L o r i n
-- 2013-01-14T21:39:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-14/yale-names-polak-as-provost-to-replace-president-elect-salovey.html
Yale University named Benjamin Polak
as provost, replacing Peter Salovey who will become the Ivy
League school’s next president on June 30.  Polak, 51, is head of Yale’s economics department,
according to a statement today by the school in New Haven,
Connecticut. Salovey takes over for Richard C. Levin, an
economist who has been president since 1993.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Janet Lorin  in New York   jlorin@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lisa Wolfson at   lwolfson@bloomberg.net . 